<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak to Develop Small Towns in Next Five Years: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 5 (Xinhua) -- A program for the development
of small and medium towns will be included in the 9th Five Year
Plan (1998-2003) of Pakistan, which is under preparation, a senior
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
In his message on the occasion of the World Habitat Day, which
is being observed on October 6, Minister of State for Environment
and Local Government Makhdoom Syed Ahmed Mahmood said that
Pakistan faces many challenges of urbanization.
</P>
<P>
These challenges included provision of shelter and services for
the inhabitants of its cities, towns and villages, said the
minister.
</P>
<P>
He said that the quality of urban environment and productivity
was not satisfactory in Pakistan, but the government was
determined to bring about a perceptible change in this area.
</P>
<P>
The theme for this year's World Habitat Day is "Future Cities".
The minister said that it offers urban residents around the global
an opportunity to reflect on the problems and challenges facing
their own cities.
</P>
<P>
It is also an opportunity for people living in cities to
reflect on how these problems can be overcome to make their cities
cleaner and sustainable, said the minister.  
</P>
</TEXT>
