<HEADLINE> Progress M-36 Cargo Ship Successfully Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The Progress M-36 cargo ship was
successfully launched by a Soyuz-U rocket-booster from the
Baikonur space center today at 19:08 Moscow time, according to the
Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The report cited sources at the Russian Space Agency as saying
that it will bring a spare computer and several tons of other
cargo to the Russian Mir orbiting station.
</P>
<P>
The cargo is 99 percent traditional -- equipment, materials,
fuel and foods. Some additional equipment for repairs of the
Spectrum module, which became depressurized after a collision of
the Mir station and the Progress M-34 cargo ship on June 25, is
also on board the Progress M-36 cargo ship.
</P>
<P>
It was said that the ship carries gifts of the Itar-Tass news
agency -- T-shirts with the Itar-Tass emblem and a letter. The
ship is expected to be docked to Mir on October 7 in an automatic
regime. The day before the docking the M-35 cargo ship will
separate from Mir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
