<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British Prime Minister Visits Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Prime Minister Tony
Blair arrived in Moscow tonight on a one-day working visit, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During the day of the visit, Blair will meet with Russian
President Boris Yeltsin, Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and
Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov.
</P>
<P>
The Russian and British leaders will focus on deepening of
bilateral cooperation in economy, science and technology, as well
as on British investments in Russia.
</P>
<P>
The sides also will discuss European security, Russia's
relations with NATO and the European Union, activities of the G-8
currently chaired by Britain, and the situation in the Middle
East, Bosnia and Herzegovina, the Baltic republics and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on anti-crime measures will be signed by
Chernomyrdin and Blair Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
After meeting Russian managers, the British premier will leave
for london Monday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
