<HEADLINE> Syrian Vice-President Reaffirms Syria's Position </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Vice-President Zuhair
Masharqa has reaffirmed that Syria is seeking to achieve
a fair and overall peace based on the U.N. resolutions, the Madrid
agreement and the land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
Masharqa made the remarks in an article published today by
Syrian newspaper Al-Baath, mouth peace of the ruling party, to
celebrate the 24th anniversary of the Arab-Israeli 1973 war.
</P>
<P>
"Since the Madrid conference was convened six years ago,
Israel has not been serious about the peace process," Masharqa
said.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian vice-president underlined the necessity of Israel's
withdrawal from all occupied Arab territories up to the June 4,
1967 boundaries.
</P>
<P>
He also called for restoring the usurped national rights and
providing peace and security for all parties in accordance with
the Madrid formula and the land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
Syria has been insisting that the Syrian-Israeli peace
negotiations should resume from where they halted in May, 1996,
but the Israeli government has said that the negotiations should
start anew without any preconditions. 
