<HEADLINE> China Daily Launches Hong Kong Edition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China Daily, the only national
English-language daily newspaper on the Chinese mainland, launched
its Hong Kong edition today.
</P>
<P>
A reception was held here today to mark the birth of the China
Daily Hong Kong edition.
</P>
<P>
Among those attending the reception were Ann Tse-kai, vice
chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultation
Conference; Zhang Junsheng, deputy director of the Xinhua News
Agency Hong Kong Branch; and Rita Fan, president of the
Provisional Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region of China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng and other senior
officials have extended their congratulations on the launch of the
edition.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1981, China Daily covers national and
international news on political, economic, cultural and social
developments.
</P>
<P>
More than 300,000 copies of the paper are distributed in China
and 150 countries and regions worldwide.
</P>
<P>
China Daily Hong Kong edition will be targeted to readers in
Hong Kong, Macao and Southeast Asia, such as government officials,
business executives, academics and tourists.
</P>
<P>
It will provide up-to-date and accurate news and information on
the policies of China's central government and political,
economic, social and cultural activities in China and Hong Kong.
</P>
