<HEADLINE> Turkish President Arrives in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel arrived in Kuwait today for a two-day official visit aimed
at expanding economic relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Demirel was greeted at the international airport by Kuwaiti
Emir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah, acting Prime Minister and
Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah and other
high-ranking Kuwaiti officials.
</P>
<P>
This was Demirel's second visit to Kuwait since 1991. His last
visit came in 1993 when he was Turkish prime minister.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Demirel is expected to hold talks with the
Kuwaiti Emir on further boosting the bilateral ties. The two
countries are expected to sign an agreement on the prevention of
double taxation and a cultural exchange program.
</P>
<P>
Turkey supported Kuwait in the 1991 Gulf War which liberated
Kuwait from the seven-month Iraqi occupation and adopted a firm
position toward the Iraqi invasion. Since then the two countries
exchanged many official visits.
</P>
<P>
The two states signed a memorandum of understanding on
exchanging expertise in the agricultural field and setting up
joint agricultural ventures in 1993.
</P>
<P>
They have also been bound by an agreement for the promotion and
protection of investment since 1988.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between the two countries was 200 million
U.S. dollars in 1996 with Turkish exports to Kuwait standing at
130 million dollars and Kuwait exports to Turkey at 70 million
dollars. 
</P>
