<HEADLINE> Taliban Order Destruction of Pictures, Dolls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
today ordered the destruction of all images of animals and the
Christian symbol of the crucifix in Taliban-controlled areas, a
report reaching here from Kabul said today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the Taliban also ordered the destruction of
toys that resemble living creatures.
</P>
<P>
"All pictures of animals and images of the crucifix hung or
kept in houses, shops or other places have to be eliminated as of
Monday," the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest Taliban rule, all sign painters who
decorate buildings or vehicles must cease drawing the images of
people and animals or else face punishment.
</P>
<P>
"All the spare part shops or other shops in Kabul city or
provinces should not hang paper pictures or plastic toys made in
the form of living images for children," the report added.
</P>
<P>
Since there are some Christians living in Afghanistan, the
Taliban also ordered the destruction of the Christian symbol of
the cross.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban have already banned photography and filming of
living creatures with the exception of passport photos used for
official identification purposes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
