<HEADLINE> Mongolian Opposition Insists on Resignation of Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's major opposition
party -- the Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party (MPRP) --
today reiterated its call for resignation of the incumbent
government.
</P>
<P>
The call was made at a press conference by Nambaryn Enhbayar,
chairman of the MPRP and the MPRP parliamentarian group in the
Great Hural (Mongolian parliament).
</P>
<P>
The MPRP parliamentarians had submitted a draft proposal to the
Great Hural on Saturday, urging the incumbent government led by
the Mongolian Democratic Union (MDU) to resign.
</P>
<P>
Enhbayar criticized the ruling MDU, which comprises the
Mongolian National Democratic Party and the Mongolian Social
Democratic Party, for implementing radical reform policies, which
led to the economic deterioration and the drop of people's living
standards.
</P>
<P>
He also denounced the allegedly rampant nepotism in the
appointment and removal of government officials.
</P>
<P>
So far, there are 50 MDU members and 25 MPRP members in the
76-member Great Hural. Under Mongolia's law, the Great Hural must
hold a special meeting to discuss resignation of government if it
is requested to do so by at least one fourth of the
parliamentarians.
</P>
<P>
Enhbayar said that 23 MPRP parliamentarians had signed the
draft proposal of resignation of the government, except two
visiting abroad.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, the Great Hural should discuss the proposal
within 14 days and put it to vote by secret ballot, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Then the incumbent government must be dismissed if the proposal
wins a simple majority votes, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
