<HEADLINE> World's Largest Toy Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGDONG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Zhujiang Delta in south
China's Guangdong Province recently emerged as the world's largest
toy production base.
</P>
<P>
Zhujiang accounted for a major portion of Guangdong Province's
total export value for toys during the first half of this
year. The delta's toy export value of 1.45 billion US dollars
represented a 36 percent year-on-year rise and accounted for
75 percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, China's major toy exporter, exported toys valued
at 812 million US dollars in 1996, with a mere 1.12 percent of
total products receiving unqualified classifications.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's toy production meets the needs of the international
market, with the province currently producing the vast majority of
products for most major toy manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
China has emerged as a major exporter of high-quality toys to
the United States, and currently accounts for over half of the
imported toys on the US market.
</P>
<P>
Seven of the top ten most popular toys in 1996 were produced by
the Guangdong Zhentai Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
