<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts '97 Urban Environment Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Second Urban Environment
Forum - UEF '97, jointly sponsored by the United Nations Center
for Human Settlements (UNCHS-HABITAT) and United Nations
Environmental Program (UNEP), opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Some 200 participants from both at home and abroad are
representing 30 Chinese and some 70 foreign cities, as well as 30
international organizations.
</P>
<P>
The forum will focus on the most effective use of limited
resources to promote urban environmental management. Participants
will discuss various approaches to implementing the 21st Century
Agenda and practical methods for developing the urban
environmental plan and management.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations designated the first monday in October as
the annual World Day of Human Settlements.
</P>
<P>
This year's topic for World Day of Human Settlements will focus
on future cities. The United Nations predicts that future cities
will offer adequate housing, healthy and safe environments, basic
services and job opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The First Urban Environment Forum - UEF '96 was held in
Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government of Shanghai, China's largest
industrial city, has steadfastly promoted the city's environmental
plan and management in line with economic development in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has been listed as one of the first pilot cities to
carry out China's 21st Century Agenda. 
</P>
