<HEADLINE> Uganda to Upgrade Weather Stations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan Meteorological
Department has received a fund of 30,000 Pounds (some 50,000 U.S.
Dollars) from the World Meteorological Organization for
rehabilitating 27 weather stations, reported "The Monitor" today.
</P>
<P>
A. R. Otte, the principal meteorologist of Uganda, said the
rehabilitation will start with Mubende Weather Station in the
center which he was inspecting recently.
</P>
<P>
