Congratulating Locke on becoming the first Chinese-American
governor of a US state and welcoming him on his first China tour
since assuming office, Jiang said Washington state is a big state
in the US which cherishes close ties with Asia and has enjoyed
increasing economic and trade contacts with China in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed more businessmen from Washington state, saying he
believed Locke's ongoing visit would be sure to deepen involvement
between China and Washington state.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Locke accepted Jiang's congratulations,
saying he is proud of being an American and of his Chinese origin.
</P>
<P>
In the past two decades, he said, China has scored
world-acclaimed progress and the people's living standard has
improved, both of which are pleasing to Chinese throughout the
world.
</P>
<P>
He noted his state cherishes a long history of relations with
China and has a very good basis for bilateral economic and trade
contacts and mutual friendship.
</P>
<P>
During his term of office, he wants to promote exchanges and
cooperation in various fields between Washington state and China,
the governor said.
</P>
<P>
He stated that the American people are looking forward to
Jiang's forthcoming visit to the US. He wished good results for
the US-China summit and complete success for Jiang's US tour.
</P>
<P>
Locke is in China as guest of the government of southwest
China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Present at today's meeting were Qi Huaiyuan, president of the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign
Countries, and Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign Affairs Office
of the State Council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
