<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Expands Settlement Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank has
seen its settlement business forge ahead rapidly as a result of
the nationwide electronic hook-up of its settlement systems a year
ago.
</P>
<P>
The bank has transferred more than three trillion yuan-worth of
money through its electronic settlement system among its more than
8,000 branch banks and representative offices nationwide between
October 1996 and last September. This translates into a daily
average of more than 13 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
It also became the 57th settlement bank for the International
Air Transportation Association (IATA), with more than 126 of its
branch banks conducting settlement for the association and
involving a total of 40 international airlines from more than 20
countries. Its settlement volume for the association reaches
billions of yuan a day.
</P>
<P>
The bank also won the bid to become the settlement bank of the
China Commodities Trading Center last May, which experts said was
a big step forward for the bank's settlement business.
</P>
<P>
The China Construction Bank has also conducted settlement deals
for numerous large enterprise groups and some securities
companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
