Qian said he appreciated Locke's efforts to promote the Sino-US
relations and to enhance bilateral economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that as China has huge markets and the US has
advanced technology, both sides should continue to expand
bilateral economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed Chinese President Jiang Zemin's upcoming
visit to the US later this month would certainly push bilateral
relations to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Increasing contacts between the people of the two countries is
conducive to the advancement of bilateral relations, Qian said,
adding he hoped that Chinese provinces and US states would forge
more direct and cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
Locke said he is ready to continue to promote the US-China
relations, in particular the exchanges and cooperation between
Washington state and Chinese businesses.
</P>
<P>
Locke is in China as guest of the government of southwest
China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
