industrials added 6.2 to 4545.6.
</P>
<P>
Shares in Crown Casino rose three cents to close at 1.55
Australian dollars following its announcement this morning that it
had reached agreement with Hudson Conway to acquire the casino
management contract at Melbourne's Crown Casino.
</P>
<P>
John Fairfax moved up three cents to 3.43 Australian dollars
after the newspaper publisher and Dow Jones revealed they were
joining forces to create and market a customized business research
and news alert service for Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
Among other industrial stocks, Rupert Murdoch's Newscorp
climbed 11 cents to 6.96 Australian dollars and its preferred
shares ended 14 cents better at 6.04 Australian dollars.
</P>
