<HEADLINE> Over 16 Million Stock Trading Accounts In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- More than 16 million stock
investors have opened trading accounts at the Shanghai Stock
Exchange, Shanghai Securities News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The number of stock investors with trading accounts stood at
16.5 million as of late September, 38 percent more than at the end
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Experts note that as stock prices get more stable, the pace at
which new trading accounts are opened slows down. In the
four-and-a-half-month period since May, a total of 1.9 million
investors opened trading accounts, which was a daily increase of
only a third of April's rate.
</P>
<P>
China has two stock exchanges, the other one being in Shenzhen,
the special economic zone next to Hong Kong. By the end of August
there were 708 listed companies in China, with a combined 159.7
billion shares and a market capitalization of 1.64 trillion yuan,
about 24 percent of China's gross domestic product.  
</P>
