of more than 7.5 billion U.S. dollars in the last fiscal year from
March 21, 1996 to March 20, 1997, local Persian daily Hamshahri
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Quoting the Central Bank of Iran (CBI), the newspaper said that
Iran's export in the fiscal stood at 22.49 billion dollars while
import at 14.97 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the CBI announced that Iran has reduced its foreign debt
by 23.2 percent to 16.83 billion dollars in the last fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total foreign debt, 12.27 billion dollars was in the
form of medium and long-term loans and the remainder short-term
loans, the report said.
</P>
<P>
However, it said Iran's total long-term debt by March 21, 1997
would actually reach 32.6 billion dollars if taking into account
the due interest and letters of credit for goods it had to pay.
</P>
<P>
During the current fiscal year, Iran has to pay 8.44 billion
dollars in loan installments. The figure will be drastically
reduced to 4.45 billion dollars in the next fiscal year starting
March 21, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
