<HEADLINE> Two More Die in Violence in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Two more people were
killed on Sunday night in the Richmond area of Kwazulu-Natal,
South Africa, bringing the toll to eight since violence resumed
on Saturday night, South African Press Association reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the two United Democratic Movement members were
found early Monday, the report quoted the police as said.
</P>
<P>
Six people were killed in four separate attacks overnight
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Richmond area had seen frequent clashes between supporters
of the African National Congress and the Zulu-based Inkatha
Freedom Party (IFP), according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Kwazulu-Natal is the sole province in the hands of the IFP.
</P>
<P>
The two killed on Sunday were identified as Michael Maci
Mchunu, 31, and Tiki Chiya, 38. Both were killed at around 8 p.m.
(1800 GMT), according to police estimates.
</P>
<P>
The new wave of attacks came at a time when peace was
gradually finding its foothold in the region after months of
large-scale violence earlier this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
