<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Attack Police Post in Eastern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Six police personnel were killed
and 15 others injured today when Tamil rebels attacked a police
post in Ampara district in Eastern province of Sri Lanka,
according to the military spokesman here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Aranthalawa police post in Ampara
district  was attacked by about 100 Tamil rebels in the early
hours today.
</P>
<P>
He also said the attackers came at 23:30 Sunday. Intensive
fighting continued till 3 a.m. today. The bodies of six policemen
were recovered and 15 others attached to the post were injured and
another five are reportedly missing in the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a guerrilla war for a
separate state in the north and east of the island country since
1983. 
