<HEADLINE> Mexico Beats El Salvador 5-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Mexico came closer to
assuring itself a World Cup qualifying berth Sunday with a
lopsided 5-0 victory over El Salvador in Concacaf division
qualifying play.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's victory places Mexico at the top of the Concacaf
division with 14 of the 16 points needed to qualify.
</P>
<P>
Mexico opened the scoring at the 30th minute through Benjamin
Galindo.
</P>
<P>
Alberto Garcia Aspe upped the score to 2-0 five minutes later
and Galindo followed up on a penalty shot at the 38th minute to
bring the score to 3-0 at the half.
</P>
<P>
It was a rough day for Salvadoran goalkeeper Misael Alfaro,
with Mexico's Roberto Alves ``Zague'' scoring on a driving shot at
48 minutes and Luis Garcia at 81. However, Alfaro was able to
block a Mexican penalty kick early in the game.
</P>
<P>
Mexico now tops the Concacaf with six games played, and needs
only a tie during its next match, an October 12 meeting with
Canada in Edmonton, Alberta to qualify.
</P>
<P>
Jamaica is second at 12 points on eight games played. The
United States, in third place, has 10 points on seven games. El
Salvador has gained 9 points in eight matches, Costa Rica eight
points in eight games and Canada five points in seven games.
</P>
<P>
The top three teams from the division will qualify for the cup.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's game was played before an estimated 110,000 fans at
Mexico City's Guillermo Canedo White stadium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
