<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Urban Students Interested In Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Students in China's Zhejiang
Province have shown new interest in farming and are choosing
universities with agriculture majors.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang Agriculture University, one of the best of its kind in
the coastal province, enrolled a record 2,667 students this year,
according to the Provincial Education Commission.
</P>
<P>
Most of its 731 new undergraduates are from key high schools in
the province, and 36.3 percent are urban residents, according to
university officials.
</P>
<P>
Chinese university graduates can automatically become urban
residents and many rural young people regard higher education as
the only means of freeing themselves from the burden of farming.
</P>
<P>
Today's young people however view agriculture as a flourishing
industry, and the study of biotechnology and advanced agricultural
technology has become fashionable among some high school students.
</P>
<P>
"Modern agriculture has never relied on traditional tools such
as hoes and rakes. So I must try hard to learn advanced technology
at the agricultural university," said one student who has done
very well in the entrance exam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
