<HEADLINE> Fear Grips City Residents in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Fear gripped residents in
Cotabato city, the southern Philippines, after two grenade
throwing incidents occurred early today and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A hand grenade was found at the gate of a bus company this
morning and was defused by bomb disposal experts, reports reaching
here said.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the grenade, wrapped in a plastic, was
discovered by a bus dispatcher who at first mistook it for
garbage.
</P>
<P>
Probers said that the incident has something to do with
extortion activities. At least seven bombing incidents against the
firm have been reported in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
A day earlier in the same city, a grenade was thrown at a
residence and destroyed a portion of the roof of the house. No one
was reported hurt in the incident.
</P>
<P>
Probers allayed the fear of city residents, saying the
incidents rooted from two separate motives and would not trigger a
barrage of violence in the city. 
