<HEADLINE> Feed Producer Cutting Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Hope Group, A major feed
producer in southwest China's Sichuan province, recently cut the
prices of its products in the Shanghai Municipality and Jiangsu
and Zhejiang provinces.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of the group's effort to cut the price of its
products in three provinces and municipalities each month. It
started in March, and in the first half of the year, cumulative
price cuts amounted to 30 million yuan. Hope's market share in
East China, where more than a quarter of its subsidiaries are
located, has risen 2 percentage points, with sales of 80,000 tons
of feed.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 50,000 households involved in pig raising
in Shanghai, Jiangsu, and Zhejiang that use Hope feed, and thanks
to the price reduction, they now spend 87 yuan less on average to
raise a pig.
</P>
<P>
President Liu Yongxing of the Hope Group said the price cut is
meant to establish an image of Hope feed as a product with more
desirable price and quality that competes with imported products.
</P>
<P>
The reduction also plays an important role in limiting the
price of meat and meat products, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
Hope had annual sales worth 4.5 billion yuan last year. It has
6 percent of the nation's feed market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
