<HEADLINE> 1,600 Small Factories in Southwest China Closed for Polluting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
province has closed 1,633 small factories that caused serious
pollution since August of last year.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial government official, that is 99
percent of the province's small factories, many of which consumed
large amounts of resources and caused pollution.
</P>
<P>
The factories include paper mills and leather, dye, and coking
factories. More than a dozen medium-sized and small rivers in the
province have cleared up after the factories were shut.
</P>
<P>
Closing them means a reduction of the 92 million tons of
industrial waste water, 6.5 billion cubic meters of waste gas, and
1.4 million tons of waste residue annually.
</P>
<P>
The official added that the provincial environmental protection
departments are doing constant checks on factories to see that
they don't start up operations again. 
</P>
</TEXT>
