<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Cities And Urbanites in China Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Urban population in China rose
to 515.11 million by the end of last year, about 43 percent of its
total population, according to the latest statistics of the State
Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Of China's 666 cities, 11 have a population of more than two
million each. Next come 23 with a population of one to two
million, 44 with 500,000 to a million people, 159 with 200,000 to
500,000 people, and 393 cities with less than 200,000.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six cities were established just last year, 18 of them
in central and western parts of China. Experts say that this
indicates a faster rate of urbanization in central and western
areas, compared with economically-developed coastal areas in the
east. 
</P>
