<HEADLINE> New Delhi Becoming a Hot Transit Point for Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 6 (Xinhua) -- India's Capital New Delhi is
becoming a hot transit point for drugs going from South Asia to
the lucrative markets in Europe and America, the Hindustan Times
said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, one-sixth of the total amount of drugs
coming to New Delhi come from the "Golden Crescent" comprising
India, Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1995, 942 kg, and in 1996, 629
kg of the total heroin that was recovered in New Delhi had come
from the +Golden Crescent". Nearly 5 kg of heroin comes to Delhi
everyday from Pakistan and Afghanistan. At least 30 kg of smack
also come to the capital regularly.
</P>
<P>
Women are being increasingly used to transport drugs as they
generally don't arouse suspicion. In 1996, of the total 827 drug
smugglers arrested, 47 were women. 22 women drug smugglers were
arrested in the first four months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The police have stepped up checks and raids to curb the
increasing trend of drug smuggling via Delhi.  
</P>
</TEXT>
