<HEADLINE> China Has Over 8,000 Centenarians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Out of China's 1.2 billion
people, more than 8,000 have lived for more than a century,
according to the Chinese National Committee on Aging.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China has 120 million people above the age
of 60, and more than 20 million above 70, and eight million above
80.
</P>
<P>
China reportedly adds 3.2 percent annually to its above-60
population, and those above 80 are increasing at an annual rate of
5.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
People at the committee on aging attribute the growth of the
aging population mainly to improved living standards and medical
care in the past two decades.  
</P>
