<HEADLINE> Liberian Arrested on Beijing Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Beijing police have arrested
five people, one of whom is a Liberian, and charged them with
defrauding people by using fake US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Forfee Marvie, a Liberian citizen, and four other persons said
that they deceived passers-by into buying the fake dollars,
according to the municipal public security sources. They passed
themselves off as relatives of a Liberian national bank governor,
claiming that in order to get a large amount of US dollars out of
Liberia, which was alleged to be unstable politically, they had
put black ink on the money, and potential buyers were told that
the black could be easily removed after it was treated with a
special fluid.
</P>
<P>
But, the so-called dollars were simply pieces of black paper
and the special fluid was just a mixture of water and vitamin C,
the police said after investigating the incident.
</P>
<P>
Beijing police warned residents to be careful of being fooled
by swindlers of this kind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
