<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Government to Set Up Industry Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh Government has
decided to set up a 45.45-million-U.S.-dollar special fund only
for industrial financing, the independent United News Agency (UNB)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The government will provide a half of the money for the
Industrial Development Fund while the Bangladesh Bank, the central
bank of the country, will funnel a same amount into the exclusive
fund in order to stimulate industrialization, the UNB said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, foreign banks will provide loans to
industrial projects, mainly in the manufacturing sector, while the
Industrial Fund channel the matching funds, the UNB added.
</P>
<P>
As 50 percent of the total loans will be provided from the
Fund, the UNB continued, the total amount to be invested under the
special scheme will be bout 90.90 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by the government because the business
community recently alleged that the long-term loans for setting up
industries became scarce for them and the liquidity shortage in
the banks threatened the country's industrialization process, the
news agency explained.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh Government has also decided to take up a special
program for industrial financing and decided in principle to float
an industrial bond to raise at least 113 million dollars to
provide long-term industrial loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
