<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Romania and the United States
have found feasible plans for strategic partnership, a U.S.
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Marc Grossman, U.S. Assistant Secretary for Canadian and
European Affairs, made the remark after meeting Romanian President
Emil Constantinescu, Prime Minister Victor Ciorbea, Defense
Minister Victor Babiuc and Foreign Minister Adrian Severin.
</P>
<P>
A joint communique released today said that the
Romanian-U.S. strategic partnership aims to strengthen their
political and econmic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed cooperation in intelligence.
</P>
