<HEADLINE> Private Sector in Hebei Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The private sector in the
Economic and Technological Development Zone of Qinhuangdao, a
scenic spot in China's Hebei province, has been developing hi-tech
products.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 100 private enterprises in the zone in
technology-related businesses, accounting for half the zone's
private sector.
</P>
<P>
The Haiwan Safety Technology Co. Ltd., set up by four
university grads has developed 82 types of fire-alarm systems that
are doing well both in China and abroad, and the company now ranks
among the province's "Top Ten Enterprises". Its 1996 output was
worth 100 million yuan, and its fixed assets amounted to 12
million yuan, compared to 80,000 yuan in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Some private businesses have earned a good reputation for
name-brand products in water supplies, heating, and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
Hu Yingjie, the director of the zone's Administrative
Committee, attributes the development to good local environmental
conditions, the large number of professionals with a higher
education who are in the zone's private sector, and to
preferential policies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
