<HEADLINE> Russia Wins European Volleyball Women's Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Russia breezed through Croatia in
three sets to capture the women's title of the European Volleyball
Championship in Brno, Czech Republic, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Russians cracked the Croat team 15-7 in the first set in 17
minutes. The Croats tried to turn the table in the second set, but
they could not match the Russians powerful spikes and had to settle
a set 12-15 in 32 minute.
</P>
<P>
In the final set, Croatia jumped to a 5-1 lead, but the
Russians quickly controlled the game and won the rubber 15-9.
</P>
<P>
The Czech squad, which beat Bulgaria 15-13, 15-10, 15-7
Saturday, wrapped up the bronze. 
</P>
