<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, October 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Shuttle Atlantis's landing on the earth was
postponed by one and a half hours Sunday evening because of gusty
wind and thick clouds, the National Aeronautics and Space
Administration (NASA) said.
</P>
<P>
NASA ordered the seven-member shuttle crew to stay up an extra
orbit and try for a touchdown later in the evening as the wind was
too gusty and the clouds were too thick for the Atlantis to land
safely.
</P>
<P>
The shuttle was scheduled to land at the Kennedy Space Center
in Florida at 6:59 p.m. EDT (2259 GMT).
(US-Atlantis-Landing-Delay)
