<HEADLINE> Yellow River Tourism Project Attracts Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Xiaolangdi Water Control
Project on the Yellow River has attracted a new source of foreign
investment for the development of tourism resources.
</P>
<P>
The Adorna Group of Malaysia and a tourism company in Henan
Province recently announced plans for a cooperative project.
</P>
<P>
The project in the Huanglu Mountains, Mengjin County, will
cover 80 ha and involve a total investment of 80 million US
dollars. Adorna will provide 70 percent of the total
investment. First phase construction will cost 15 million US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The partners will build recreational facilities, including a
boat dock, a sight-seeing platform and vacation villa complex.
</P>
<P>
The site is located 40 km from the Henan capital of Luoyang, a
city which served as the capital for nine dynasties in ancient
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
