<HEADLINE> Tchmil Wins Paris-Tours Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Andrei Tchmil of Ukraine claimed
the victory of the Paris-Tours cycling race and became the first
former Soviet to win the classic French race in Tours on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Tchmil and Max Sciandri of Britain both broke away in the final
five kilometers after overtaking Maurizio Fondriest of
Italy. Tchmil reeled over Sciandri in the final sprint.
</P>
<P>
Australian Henk Vogels was third with five seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
The race was 254.5 kilometers from Saint-Arnoult-en-Yveslines,
south of Paris, to Tours.
</P>
<P>
The next World Cup race is the Tour of Lombardy on October 19.
</P>
</TEXT>
