<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest Chinese Mothers Declare War Against White Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Some 10,000 women in northwest
China's Shaanxi province have volunteered their services for a
campaign against "white pollution", mainly resulting from
discarded plastic waste.
</P>
<P>
The campaign began last month and will last until next
March. The purpose of launching such a campaign is to make a
cleaner and tidier environment in rural and urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The last Saturday of each month has been set aside for a group
of mothers to pick up rubbish in public places and to plant trees
and grass to beautify their communities.
</P>
<P>
The mothers have also been asked to use more objects that do
not cause pollution in their daily lives and to put garbage into
different categories by bag.
</P>
<P>
The campaign is sponsored by provincial government departments
and local mass organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
