<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shuttle Atlantis Delays Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Shuttle Atlantis's landing on
the earth was postponed by one and a half hours this evening
because of gusty wind and thick clouds, the National Aeronautics
and Space Administration (NASA) said.
</P>
<P>
NASA ordered the seven-member shuttle crew to stay up an extra
orbit and try for a touchdown later in the evening as the wind was
too gusty and the clouds were too thick for the Atlantis to land
safely.
</P>
<P>
The shuttle was scheduled to land at the Kennedy Space Center
in Florida at 6:59 p.m. EDT (2259 GMT).
</P>
<P>
Among the astronauts to come back was Michael Foale who has
left the earth for 144 days and stayed for four and a half months
in the Mir, the Russian space station. 
</P>
</TEXT>
