<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Faction Leader Suggests United Front </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's Islamic Party
leader Gulbuddin Hekmatyar announced here today that he is ready
to take part in a political and military united front against the
Taliban in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The visiting former Afghan prime minister added "Taliban has
effectively taken advantage of the discord amongst the Jihadi
groups. We need to resolve our differences and form a united
front."
</P>
<P>
Hekmatyar said "the war would not have a victor. The big
powers should know that no individual or country can install a
puppet government in Afghanistan."
</P>
<P>
He said that over 1 million dead, 2 million disabled and 8
million refugees are caused by the war in the country.
</P>
<P>
Taliban "won't be able to rule the country" despite its
victories in battle fields, he was quoted by Iranian official news
agency IRNA as saying.
</P>
<P>
He elaborated on his group's proposed plan for establishment
of peace in the country which hinges on demilitarization of Kabul
and the simultaneous formation of a non-coalition government in
the country.
</P>
<P>
He also warned against foreign interference in the Afghan
internal affairs and called on Iran to convince Pakistan to
stop supporting the Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
Hekmatyar is now visiting Tehran for apparent demand of Iran's
military and financial support for his group. But details on
schedule of his visit were not made public in a customary practice.
</P>
</TEXT>
